✔ Two-Pointer Merge (Optimal)
def merge(a, b):
    i = j = 0
    out = []
    while i < len(a) and j < len(b):
        if a[i] <= b[j]:
            out.append(a[i]); i += 1
        else:
            out.append(b[j]); j += 1
    out.extend(a[i:]); out.extend(b[j:])
    return out
✔ K-way Merge (Many Sources)
Use min-heap → O(N log k)
import heapq

def k_way_merge(lists):
    heap = []
    for i, lst in enumerate(lists):
        if lst:
            heap.append((lst[0], i, 0))
    heapq.heapify(heap)

    res = []
    while heap:
        val, li, idx = heapq.heappop(heap)
        res.append(val)
        if idx + 1 < len(lists[li]):
            heapq.heappush(heap, (lists[li][idx+1], li, idx+1))
    return res
✔ External Merge (Big Data)
Sort chunks → write to disk → merge streams
Used when data doesn’t fit in memory
